From: Dreeam <61569423+Dreeam-qwq@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 27 May 2026 00:38:04 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Optimize block entities count

Just use `getTickableTileEntityCount` for `getTileEntityCount` to be simpler, to reduce expensive overhead from Spark's
statistics calls.

diff --git a/src/main/java/org/bukkit/craftbukkit/CraftWorld.java b/src/main/java/org/bukkit/craftbukkit/CraftWorld.java
index 413da40e1f23fe27a1c8f2c298de5730f2a68a21..615d115b5490799233078b32a128b3c01865a4aa 100644
--- a/src/main/java/org/bukkit/craftbukkit/CraftWorld.java
+++ b/src/main/java/org/bukkit/craftbukkit/CraftWorld.java
@@ -224,6 +224,7 @@ public class CraftWorld extends CraftRegionAccessor implements World {
 
     @Override
     public int getTileEntityCount() {
+        if (org.reactive.config.modules.opt.OptimizeBlockEntities.enabled) return world.blockEntityTickers.size(); // Leaf - Optimize block entities count
         // We don't use the full world block entity list, so we must iterate chunks
         int size = 0;
         for (ChunkHolder playerchunk : ca.spottedleaf.moonrise.common.PlatformHooks.get().getVisibleChunkHolders(this.world)) {
